description.narrative: (Europe and Eurasia Regional): This will be BEP's final year of funding to help the Government of Serbia (GoS) to increase the competitiveness of the Serbian economy by streamlining the business enabling environment, improving public financial management, and strengthening financial markets. Project activities are based on priorities identified by the private sector and the GoS; critical reforms related to labor, construction permitting and inspections have been adopted with assistance from the program, but further systematic assistance and capacity development is critical to ensure the effective implementation of these reforms. At the same time, additional critical legislation, including a pending draft law on non-bank financial institutions is planned that could provide a legislative basis for a viable microfinance system in Serbia; BEP's planned assistance will play a critical role in convening key stakeholders and providing assistance to the legislative development and implementation processes.

Objectives for Serbia: The project is helping Serbia achieve reforms that will: Reduce legal and regulatory burdens on businesses; Improve macroeconomic policy and public financial management; Deepen financial market development and increase access to finance.
